insights: It's great that you're reaching out for support early in your academic journey; this proactive step shows your commitment to success. Keep this up!
Remember, it's completely normal to feel overwhelmed or unsure at this stage. Consider setting small, achievable goals each week to stay focused and motivated.
Building a study schedule that includes breaks and time for self-care can significantly improve your productivity and well-being.
Don't hesitate to connect with your professors or academic advisors for guidance; they're there to help you navigate your first year successfully.
